MBOMBELA &#8211; An accident occurred when a taxi driving towards Mozambique collided with a truck on the N4 Road between Ngodwana and Elandshoek last night.According to the provincial department of safety and security spokesman Mr Joseph Mabuza, five people were confirmed dead and four people were seriously injured and four slightly injured. &#8220;They were taken to Rob Ferreira Hospital.&#8221;He said the deceased were two adult males, two adult females and one little girl aged between five or six years old. The taxi was a Mozambican registered vehicle.Lowvelder will update with information as it becomes available.